      <akn:section eId="sec_21_2115">
        <akn:num>21-2115</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Construction of power relating to retirement plan transactions.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-2115_1">
      <akn:num>(1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Select payment options under any retirement plan in which the principal participates, including plans for self-employed individuals;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-2115_2">
      <akn:num>(2)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Designate beneficiaries under those plans and change existing designations;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-2115_3">
      <akn:num>(3)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Make voluntary contributions to those plans;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-2115_4">
      <akn:num>(4)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Exercise the investment powers available under any self-directed retirement plan;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-2115_5">
      <akn:num>(5)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Make “rollovers” of plan benefits into other retirement plans;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-2115_6">
      <akn:num>(6)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If authorized by the plan, borrow from, sell assets to, and purchase assets from the plan; and</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_21-2115_7">
      <akn:num>(7)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Waive the right of the principal to be a beneficiary of a joint or survivor annuity if the principal is a spouse who is not employed.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
